                            <comment id="12582205" author="fmeschbe" created="Wed, 26 Mar 2008 09:38:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;With the patch of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-55&quot; title=&quot;Look at migration to more recent Jetty version&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FELIX-55&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FELIX-55&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; applied, this request does not get a 302 anymore but a 404 because the target is selected by the request.getPathInfo() which is null in case of a direct access. Fixing this by checking for this null situation.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12582210" author="fmeschbe" created="Wed, 26 Mar 2008 09:47:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for reporting.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue is fixed in Rev. 641226 by checking for path info to be null and assuming an empty path in this case.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please close if this fixes your problem. Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
